The paper deals with the capacity region of index coding problems, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also introduces the notion of unicycle for the side information graph, which is a concept in graph theory (cs.DS) and the paper discusses the maximal acyclic induced subgraph outer bound on the capacity region, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with the removal of side information, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.SI).
